<section class="detail" id="reset/0">


  <div class="detail-header">
    <a href="#reset/0" class="detail-link" data-no-tooltip="" aria-label="Link to this function">
      <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
    <div class="heading-with-actions">

      <div class="signature-row">


            <h1 class="signature" translate="no">reset()<span class="signature-arrow">&nbsp;-&gt;&nbsp;</span><span class="signature-result"><a href="unicode.html#t:chardata/0">unicode:chardata</a>()</span></h1>



          <span class="note">(since OTP @OTP-20028@)</span>


          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/stdlib/src/io_ansi.erl#L2056" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">



<p>Reset virtual terminal sequences to their original state.</p><p>This only resets the things supported by the loaded terminfo database,
which means that OSCs such as <a href="#hyperlink_start/2"><code class="inline">hyperlink_start/2</code></a> are not reset but have
to be reset by emitting <a href="#hyperlink_reset/0"><code class="inline">hyperlink_reset/0</code></a>.</p><p>Example:</p><pre><code class="makeup erlang" translate="no"><span class="gp unselectable">1&gt; </span><span class="nc">io_ansi</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">reset</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0827150337-1">(</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0827150337-1">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0827150337-2">&lt;&lt;</span><span class="s">&quot;\e(B\e[m&quot;</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0827150337-2">&gt;&gt;</span></code></pre>
  </section>
</section>
